Step 1: Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Debt is taken as Total Liabilities. In this balance sheet, only Total Current Liabilities are provided, which is 1,903,121.89.  
• Total Owner’s Equity at the end date is 29,250,911.98.  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 1,903,121.89 / 29,250,911.98  
  ≈ 0.06507 → Rounded to two decimal places gives 0.07.

Step 2: Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit from the income statement is 1,250,911.98.  
• Total Revenue is 18,062,437.45.  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (1,250,911.98 / 18,062,437.45) × 100  
  ≈ 6.927% → Rounded to two decimal places gives 6.93%.

Step 3: Calculate Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities from the cash flow statement is –13,358,400.82.  
• Total Current Liabilities is 1,903,121.89.  
• Operating Cash Flow to Current Liabilities Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Current Liabilities  
  = –13,358,400.82 / 1,903,121.89  
  ≈ –7.016 → Rounded to two decimal places gives –7.02.

Now, in the required JSON format the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.07",
    "Net Profit Margin": "6.93%",
    "operating cash flow to current liabilities ratio": "-7.02"
  }
}
